# Update Context Files

Use this file with any coding assistant to refresh `.ai/context/` as the project evolves, without re-running the full bootstrap workflow.

## When to Run

Run an update when:

- database schema changes
- API endpoints are added or removed
- roles or permissions change
- important directories, entry points, or scripts move
- framework/runtime versions drift
- the generated context looks stale

## Workflow

1. Read `.ai/update/README.md` for the full update strategy
2. Inspect `.ai/context/` and `.ai/update/.last-updated`
3. Re-scan the codebase for current schema, endpoints, roles, glossary terms, and project structure
4. Present a change report before applying updates
5. Update structured data files directly when approved
6. Suggest diffs for prose files instead of overwriting them blindly
7. Summarize what changed and recommend committing the updated `.ai/` output

## Starter Prompt

```text
Use .ai/update/README.md and .ai/update/UPDATE.md to refresh the generated context files. Re-scan the repository, show me the drift, and only apply approved updates.
```
